00:39:28,041 --> 00:39:30,251
- She have much cash?
- I don't believe so.

977
00:39:30,376 --> 00:39:32,587
I give her money,
but she keeps losing it.

978
00:39:34,088 --> 00:39:35,757
Is this the first time
she's left you?

979
00:39:35,882 --> 00:39:36,799
What do you mean by that?

980
00:39:36,925 --> 00:39:39,344
Oh, come, come, come, my boy.
I'm married, too.

981
00:39:39,469 --> 00:39:41,679
Now, has she ever done
anything like this before?

982
00:39:41,804 --> 00:39:45,808
No. No, she locked me out
a few times, but that's all.

983
00:39:45,934 --> 00:39:48,519
Hello.
Hello, the Green Cab Company?

984
00:39:48,645 --> 00:39:50,688
I know this is
against your rules,

985
00:39:50,813 --> 00:39:52,357
but I-I certainly
would appreciate it

986
00:39:52,482 --> 00:39:53,900
if you could help me out.

987
00:39:54,025 --> 00:39:57,528
Uh, did you get a call last
night from 324 Adam Street?

988
00:39:57,654 --> 00:40:00,281
Look, I told you once,
it's against rules.

989
00:40:00,406 --> 00:40:04,369
Well, I'm not her husband,
you see, I'm her father.

990
00:40:04,494 --> 00:40:06,079
And, uh, she's â€”

991
00:40:06,204 --> 00:40:08,289
Well, she's, uh â€”

992
00:40:08,414 --> 00:40:10,875
She's expecting, uh, you know,

993
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:13,753
and you know how they are
in that condition.

994
00:40:13,878 --> 00:40:15,797
Sometimes they do â€”

995
00:40:15,922 --> 00:40:17,590
If you could find it
in your heart to help me,

996
00:40:17,715 --> 00:40:18,841
I certainly would appreciate it.

997
00:40:20,259 --> 00:40:21,344
Well...

998
00:40:23,596 --> 00:40:24,889
there was a call.

999
00:40:25,014 --> 00:40:26,391
Where did you take her?

1000
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:30,186
Thanks, thanks very, very much.

1001
00:40:30,311 --> 00:40:31,688
We won't forget this.

1002
00:40:31,813 --> 00:40:32,689
Where'd she go?

1003
00:40:32,814 --> 00:40:34,607
- Home.
- Home?

1004
00:40:34,732 --> 00:40:36,567
Home? What do you mean, home?
This is her home.

1005
00:40:36,693 --> 00:40:39,153
Oh, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
I mean my home. Come on.

1006
00:40:39,278 --> 00:40:40,989
I'll wait here.

1007
00:40:41,114 --> 00:40:43,866
Do you want her to come back
or don't you?

1008
00:40:43,992 --> 00:40:45,118
Yes.

1009
00:40:45,243 --> 00:40:47,203
Well, then you'll have to
go and get her.

1010
00:40:47,328 --> 00:40:48,788
That's the first law
of marriage.

1011
00:40:48,913 --> 00:40:51,207
You can't expect
any self-respecting wife

1012
00:40:51,332 --> 00:40:53,626
to come home
under her own power.

1013
00:41:04,679 --> 00:41:07,890
I don't suppose you want to tell
me what the quarrel was about?

1014
00:41:08,016 --> 00:41:10,351
If you don't mind,
I'd rather not talk about it.

1015
00:41:10,476 --> 00:41:11,602
Okay.

1016
00:41:14,355 --> 00:41:15,523
I don't know whether
you know it,

1017
00:41:15,648 --> 00:41:18,151
but your daughter's
got a terrible temper.

1018
00:41:18,276 --> 00:41:19,527
I'm sorry.

1019
00:41:19,652 --> 00:41:22,196
And this business tonight,
why, it's like a child,

1020
00:41:22,321 --> 00:41:23,698
and a spoiled child at that.

1021
00:41:23,823 --> 00:41:24,824
She's got to grow up.

1022
00:41:24,949 --> 00:41:26,284
She's got to be made to realize

1023
00:41:26,409 --> 00:41:27,660
that she can't go
running home to you

1024
00:41:27,785 --> 00:41:29,871
every time there's something
that she doesn't like.

1025
00:41:32,790 --> 00:41:35,710
Well, what do you want me to do?
Pack up and move?

1026
00:42:30,473 --> 00:42:32,642
- Hi, Pops.

1027
00:42:41,150 --> 00:42:44,195
Forgot your key, I suppose.
Why didn't you ring?

1028
00:42:44,320 --> 00:42:45,822
Oh.

1029
00:42:47,532 --> 00:42:49,575
I didn't want to wake up
you and Moms.

1030
00:42:50,993 --> 00:42:52,620
Anyway, I â€”

1031
00:42:52,745 --> 00:42:55,081
Doctor told me to sleep
with plenty of fresh air.

1032
00:42:55,206 --> 00:42:57,250
Well, you certainly had your
share for tonight, I guess.

1033
00:42:57,375 --> 00:42:58,584
Come on.

1034
00:42:58,709 --> 00:43:01,963
First, I-I want you
to know this, Pops.

1035
00:43:02,088 --> 00:43:03,506
I've left Buckley.

1036
00:43:03,631 --> 00:43:05,258
I've left him for good.

1037
00:43:06,801 --> 00:43:08,344
I wish you'd tell Moms for me.

1038
00:43:08,469 --> 00:43:10,054
Ask her not to fuss.

1039
00:43:11,013 --> 00:43:12,181
It's no use.

1040
00:43:13,516 --> 00:43:15,268
It's over for good now.

1041
00:43:17,103 --> 00:43:19,981
I'd rather not
have to talk about it.

1042
00:43:20,106 --> 00:43:22,358
Alright, kitten, it'll be
however you want it.

1043
00:43:22,483 --> 00:43:23,818
You know that.

1044
00:43:23,943 --> 00:43:26,445
Come on, I'll have your room
ready for you in a jiffy.

1045
00:43:27,947 --> 00:43:32,034
Oh, Pops, why did it
have to end like this?

1046
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:34,620
Everything was
so wonderful at first.

1047
00:43:34,745 --> 00:43:37,790
I felt fine.
Everybody was so sweet to me.

1048
00:43:39,667 --> 00:43:42,211
It takes too long, that's all.

1049
00:43:42,336 --> 00:43:44,130
Drags on too long.

1050
00:43:46,424 --> 00:43:48,134
I'm ugly now.

1051
00:43:48,259 --> 00:43:49,385
I'm clumsy.

1052
00:43:49,510 --> 00:43:51,929
Oh, darling.
Darling, don't say that.

1053
00:43:52,054 --> 00:43:53,806
Don't you know that
you have a beauty now

1054
00:43:53,931 --> 00:43:55,641
that you never had before?

1055
00:43:56,392 --> 00:43:58,394
I know what I look like.

1056
00:43:58,519 --> 00:44:01,856
I'm dull and stupid.

1057
00:44:01,981 --> 00:44:04,692
I can't do any
of the things I used to do.

1058
00:44:06,235 --> 00:44:08,654
Now when I need him most,
I've lost him.

1059
00:44:09,739 --> 00:44:11,115
Doesn't love me anymore.

1060
00:44:11,240 --> 00:44:13,284
Oh, kitten, you mustn't
think things like that.

1061
00:44:13,409 --> 00:44:15,870
He loves you more than ever.
He's frantic with worry.

1062
00:44:15,995 --> 00:44:17,747
Well, he just said to me
if anything happened to you,

1063
00:44:17,872 --> 00:44:19,332
he'd kill himself.

1064
00:44:21,834 --> 00:44:23,252
What do you mean?

1065
00:44:23,377 --> 00:44:24,795
Did he call you?

1066
00:44:24,921 --> 00:44:26,839
He's right out there now.

1067
00:44:28,591 --> 00:44:29,884
Oh!

1068
00:44:31,844 --> 00:44:33,304
I suppose he told you
everything.

1069
00:44:33,429 --> 00:44:35,848
Didn't tell me anything.
Just that you had an argument.

1070
00:44:37,099 --> 00:44:38,476
An argument?

1071
00:44:39,769 --> 00:44:41,229
That's wonderful.

1072
00:44:42,438 --> 00:44:44,065
Do you know what it really is?

1073
00:44:45,316 --> 00:44:47,026
There's someone else, Pops.

1074
00:44:47,151 --> 00:44:49,237
He's found someone else.

1075
00:44:49,362 --> 00:44:51,239
He goes off
and leaves me every night

1076
00:44:51,364 --> 00:44:55,910
and tells me he goes to
the office, but it isn't true.

1077
00:44:56,035 --> 00:44:58,204
I've called the office,
and he isn't there.

1078
00:45:00,206 --> 00:45:03,334
He's in love with someone else.

1079
00:45:06,379 --> 00:45:09,257
Oh, darling, don't, don't.

1080
00:45:09,382 --> 00:45:11,259
Please, don't, don't.

1081
00:45:12,385 --> 00:45:15,137
We'll talk about it tomorrow.
You've got to get your rest now.

1082
00:45:16,555 --> 00:45:18,224
I'll â€” I'll send him away.

1083
00:45:18,349 --> 00:45:19,767
I'll send him away.

1084
00:45:25,731 --> 00:45:27,984
She's here.
She's been asleep.

1085
00:45:28,109 --> 00:45:29,777
I wouldn't try to talk
to her if I were you

1086
00:45:29,902 --> 00:45:31,946
in the mood she's in now.

1087
00:45:32,071 --> 00:45:33,739
Did she say why we had a fight?

1088
00:45:33,864 --> 00:45:34,865
Yes.

1089
00:45:36,158 --> 00:45:39,829
Well, look, I'd like to say
something, just for the record.

1090
00:45:39,954 --> 00:45:42,081
It's not true.
Not a word of it.

1091
00:45:42,206 --> 00:45:44,083
I've been working every night.

1092
00:45:45,042 --> 00:45:48,129
After all,
we're going to have a baby.

1093
00:45:48,254 --> 00:45:50,923
You know,
I-I want to give him â€”

1094
00:45:52,258 --> 00:45:55,303
She said that she phoned me
twice there, nobody answered.

1095
00:45:55,428 --> 00:45:57,430
Believe me, it must have been
just a few minutes

1096
00:45:57,555 --> 00:45:59,140
I stepped out
for a cup of coffee.

1097
00:45:59,265 --> 00:46:02,393
I told her this again and again.
She won't believe me.

1098
00:46:02,518 --> 00:46:03,561
Well, you ought to
have more sense

1099
00:46:03,686 --> 00:46:05,146
than to argue with her
at a time like this.

1100
00:46:05,271 --> 00:46:06,897
You know she isn't herself.

1101
00:46:07,773 --> 00:46:09,859
Well, I'm not myself, either.

1102
00:46:11,110 --> 00:46:15,448
Look, I even thought of having
a man call Kay and tell her â€”

1103
00:46:16,157 --> 00:46:19,076
Then I said to myself,
"She doesn't believe me.

1104
00:46:19,201 --> 00:46:21,620
She doesn't believe me
that I'm working like crazy

1105
00:46:21,746 --> 00:46:23,831
night after night
for her and the baby.

1106
00:46:23,956 --> 00:46:26,334
She doesn't take my word for it,
then it doesn't matter."

1107
00:46:26,459 --> 00:46:28,586
It's finished anyway.
It's off. It's finished.

1108
00:46:28,711 --> 00:46:29,879
Now, wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

1109
00:46:30,004 --> 00:46:31,213
We'll all talk about this
in the morning

1110
00:46:31,339 --> 00:46:32,923
when we've had some sleep.

1111
00:46:33,049 --> 00:46:36,010
As far as I'm concerned,
there's nothing more to say.

1112
00:46:36,844 --> 00:46:38,512
May I use your phone?
I'd like to call a cab.

1113
00:46:38,637 --> 00:46:41,057
I'll drive you home just as
soon as I get Kay settled.

1114
00:46:41,182 --> 00:46:43,893
Thanks, I'd rather take a cab.

1115
00:46:44,018 --> 00:46:45,311
Suit yourself.

1116
00:46:50,649 --> 00:46:52,026
He's calling a cab.

1117
00:46:54,737 --> 00:46:57,531
I suppose he denied everything.

1118
00:46:57,656 --> 00:46:59,825
He told me his side of it.

1119
00:46:59,950 --> 00:47:02,078
Well, you don't
believe him, do you?

1120
00:47:02,203 --> 00:47:04,580
Darling, I only know
that he really loves you.

1121
00:47:04,705 --> 00:47:06,332
Oh, that isn't true.

1122
00:47:06,457 --> 00:47:07,666
He doesn't love me.

1123
00:47:07,792 --> 00:47:10,544
He doesn't care
whether I live or die.

1124
00:47:10,669 --> 00:47:12,880
Oh, I never should
have married him.

1125
00:47:13,005 --> 00:47:14,507
A little late
to think about that.

1126
00:47:14,632 --> 00:47:16,217
Uh, come on, now.

1127
00:47:16,342 --> 00:47:17,885
You really must get
your sleep, darling.

1128
00:47:18,010 --> 00:47:19,345
Come on, come on, now.
I'm gonna â€”

1129
00:47:19,470 --> 00:47:21,430
Forgive me for interrupting.

1130
00:47:21,555 --> 00:47:23,974
Your phone is out of order.

1131
00:47:24,892 --> 00:47:26,852
That's ridiculous.

1132
00:47:26,977 --> 00:47:28,521
Out of order?

1133
00:47:43,077 --> 00:47:44,370
Hello, hello, operator.

1134
00:47:45,746 --> 00:47:48,582
You take him home, Pops.
I can take care of myself.

1135
00:47:48,707 --> 00:47:49,959
Operator, opâ€”

1136
00:47:51,544 --> 00:47:53,254
You're not supposed to
carry things.

1137
00:47:53,379 --> 00:47:55,256
You know that.
I'll take 'em up.

1138
00:47:55,381 --> 00:47:56,590
We don't need your help.

1139
00:47:56,715 --> 00:47:59,385
- Do we, Father?
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

1140
00:47:59,510 --> 00:48:00,428
Here, I'll take 'em,
I'll take 'em.

1141
00:48:00,553 --> 00:48:02,138
You don't have a room
for her down here,

1142
00:48:02,263 --> 00:48:03,722
some place you could
fix up as a bedroom?

1143
00:48:03,848 --> 00:48:04,723
There's a couch
in the living room

1144
00:48:04,849 --> 00:48:06,600
if she wants to try that,
find it a little hard, maybe.

1145
00:48:06,725 --> 00:48:08,811
You know you're not supposed to
walk up and down stairs.

1146
00:48:08,936 --> 00:48:10,354
Another thing,
she's supposed to drink

1147
00:48:10,479 --> 00:48:12,106
eight glasses of water a day.

1148
00:48:12,231 --> 00:48:14,024
She forgets.
So if you could remind her.

1149
00:48:14,150 --> 00:48:15,609
- I'll try.
- And her exercise.

1150
00:48:15,734 --> 00:48:18,654
Dr. Nordell wants her to walk
two to three hours each day.

1151
00:48:18,779 --> 00:48:20,865
An hour in the morning
and an hour in the afternoon,

1152
00:48:20,990 --> 00:48:22,324
and we usually take
a walk in the evening.

1153
00:48:22,450 --> 00:48:24,118
And she's supposed to be
in bed at 9:30.

1154
00:48:24,243 --> 00:48:25,911
- I'll try to remember.
- And the calcium pills.

1155
00:48:26,036 --> 00:48:27,538
- Did you bring your pills?
- No, I forgot.

1156
00:48:27,663 --> 00:48:29,874
- I'll go home and get them.
- Won't it do in the morning?

1157
00:48:29,999 --> 00:48:31,959
I'll give them to your father
when he takes me home.

1158
00:48:32,084 --> 00:48:34,253
- Now, then, your shoes.
- Buckley, really. Buckley.

1159
00:48:34,378 --> 00:48:36,213
You know you can't
do them yourself.

1160
00:48:50,686 --> 00:48:52,271
Oh, Buckley.

1161
00:48:52,396 --> 00:48:54,273
Buckley, what's
happening to you?

1162
00:48:55,941 --> 00:48:57,651
Haven't you heard?

1163
00:48:57,776 --> 00:48:59,361
We're having a baby.

1164
00:50:10,849 --> 00:50:13,519
Stanley, Stanley.

1165
00:50:20,818 --> 00:50:22,278
Stanley, time to get up.

1166
00:50:27,575 --> 00:50:29,201
Wake up, sleepyhead.

1167
00:50:41,130 --> 00:50:44,300
As the days went on and nothing
happened, the tension mounted.

1168
00:50:45,759 --> 00:50:49,054
Buckley watched Kay
as if she were a time bomb.

1169
00:50:50,014 --> 00:50:51,390
That's a book.

1170
00:51:02,443 --> 00:51:04,320
Oh!

1171
00:51:04,445 --> 00:51:05,988
What is it, Kay?
What's the matter?

1172
00:51:06,113 --> 00:51:09,283
Oh, I reneged.

1173
00:51:09,408 --> 00:51:12,411
I had a heart
in my hand all the time.

1174
00:51:12,536 --> 00:51:14,622
I don't know what
I must be thinking about.

1175
00:51:16,790 --> 00:51:20,044
As November came and the great
event drew nearer and nearer,

1176
00:51:20,169 --> 00:51:22,296
we all waited
with bated breath.

1177
00:51:24,423 --> 00:51:26,425
- Is that the phone?
- No, dear.

1178
00:51:32,222 --> 00:51:34,224
Well, I guess I'll get
a little air.

1179
00:51:38,354 --> 00:51:40,522
- Stanley.
- Hmm?

1180
00:51:41,940 --> 00:51:44,151
As long as you're going,
would you give this to Kay?

1181
00:51:44,276 --> 00:51:46,487
Kâ€” Who said
anything about Kay?

1182
00:51:48,864 --> 00:51:50,783
I never could fool Ellie.

1183
00:51:52,534 --> 00:51:54,453
But I hoped I could fool Kay.

1184
00:52:02,336 --> 00:52:04,088
- Stanley! How are you?
- Hello, hello, hello.

1185
00:52:04,213 --> 00:52:06,173
- Hi, Pops.
- Hi.

1186
00:52:06,298 --> 00:52:09,051
Is this a beautiful night?
Did you see those stars?

1187
00:52:09,176 --> 00:52:11,053
Mom sent me over with this.

1188
00:52:11,178 --> 00:52:13,180
Oh, thanks.

1189
00:52:13,305 --> 00:52:15,849
Go on, go on, open it up.
Open it up. Don't mind us men.

1190
00:52:18,727 --> 00:52:19,853
Let me take your coat.

1191
00:52:19,978 --> 00:52:21,397
Oh, I can do it.
I can do it.

1192
00:52:21,522 --> 00:52:22,815
Well, at least let me help you.

1193
00:52:22,940 --> 00:52:24,233
Alright.

1194
00:52:29,279 --> 00:52:30,614
I'm glad you came by tonight.

1195
00:52:30,739 --> 00:52:32,157
She's awfully low.

1196
00:52:32,282 --> 00:52:34,952
- Anything wrong?
- No, no, she's just nervous.

1197
00:52:35,077 --> 00:52:36,995
I wish you'd talk to her.

1198
00:52:37,121 --> 00:52:39,081
- Oh, it's lovely.
- What is it?

1199
00:52:39,206 --> 00:52:41,291
It's a beautiful bed jacket.

1200
00:52:41,417 --> 00:52:43,127
Isn't that pretty?

1201
00:52:44,294 --> 00:52:46,380
Hmm. Ho-ho.

1202
00:52:46,505 --> 00:52:50,008
You certainly are going to knock
their eyes out at the hospital.

1203
00:52:50,134 --> 00:52:51,927
I'll go pack it right now.

1204
00:52:53,512 --> 00:52:55,389
Kay, Kay, now that your
father's here, you won't mind.

1205
00:52:55,514 --> 00:52:56,765
I'd like to get some cigarettes.

1206
00:52:56,890 --> 00:52:58,183
You don't have to
run right along, do you?

1207
00:52:58,308 --> 00:53:00,436
No, I can squeeze out
a couple of minutes, I guess.

1208
00:53:00,561 --> 00:53:01,729
I won't be long.

1209
00:53:03,313 --> 00:53:05,607
Hold everything till I get back.

1210
00:53:08,360 --> 00:53:09,737
You look wonderful, kitten.

1211
00:53:09,862 --> 00:53:11,071
Oh, I feel fine.

1212
00:53:11,196 --> 00:53:13,240
It's just Buckley.

1213
00:53:13,365 --> 00:53:16,076
I wish you'd talk to him.
He's so jittery.

1214
00:53:27,212 --> 00:53:29,298
What's he jittery about?

1215
00:53:29,423 --> 00:53:32,259
Oh, he â€” he's afraid that,

1216
00:53:32,384 --> 00:53:35,137
oh, something will go wrong.

1217
00:53:35,262 --> 00:53:37,181
Oh.

1218
00:53:37,306 --> 00:53:38,807
Shouldn't feel like that.

1219
00:53:40,184 --> 00:53:43,353
