Come on, Pops, you have your
picture taken with the baby.

1356
01:01:39,704 --> 01:01:41,331
- Oh, no, no, no, no.
- We've all had our pictures.

1357
01:01:41,456 --> 01:01:42,624
- No, no, not me.
- Come on, old man.

1358
01:01:42,749 --> 01:01:44,834
Oh, please, Pops.
Come on, just do it for me.

1359
01:01:44,960 --> 01:01:46,419
I want a picture
of the two of you together.

1360
01:01:46,544 --> 01:01:48,088
Yeah, we'll sit him right here.

1361
01:01:48,213 --> 01:01:50,215
How about that, my boy?
Is that alright with you?

1362
01:01:50,340 --> 01:01:52,384
He's smiling at you.
Hurry, Stan.

1363
01:01:52,509 --> 01:01:54,261
Catch him just like that.

1364
01:01:54,386 --> 01:01:56,846
No, no, I don't â€”
I just â€”

1365
01:01:56,972 --> 01:01:58,014
There we go.

1366
01:01:58,139 --> 01:01:59,516
Oh, no, don't give it to me.

1367
01:01:59,641 --> 01:02:00,642
No, no, you sit down.

1368
01:02:00,767 --> 01:02:02,769
Now go on,
smile at your grandfather.

1369
01:02:04,896 --> 01:02:07,399
- See, it's no use. I don't â€”
- Turn him around.

1370
01:02:07,524 --> 01:02:09,192
Turn him around
so we can see his face.

1371
01:02:09,317 --> 01:02:11,903
Come on, turn him around.
That's it. That's it.

1372
01:02:14,072 --> 01:02:16,241
Oh, see, it's a â€”
Look, look.

1373
01:02:18,576 --> 01:02:20,662
I-I mean, I-look â€”

1374
