1403
01:03:30,940 --> 01:03:33,026
Oh, come on in.

1404
01:03:34,027 --> 01:03:36,196
See, everything's alright now.

1405
01:03:36,321 --> 01:03:39,407
He's not scared anymore.
Is he, darling?

1406
01:03:39,532 --> 01:03:41,034
Now you've got a nice man here

1407
01:03:41,159 --> 01:03:43,411
and you're gonna give him
a big smile

1408
01:03:43,536 --> 01:03:45,455
'cause you're a good boy.

1409
01:03:45,580 --> 01:03:47,665
Now, look who's come to see you.

1410
01:03:47,791 --> 01:03:48,958
- Who is that, huh?
- Well.

1411
01:03:49,084 --> 01:03:50,543
Who is that?

1412
01:03:50,668 --> 01:03:53,421
Is that your grandfather?
Look.

1413
01:03:54,756 --> 01:03:57,717
Oh, honey, you terrible child.

1414
01:04:00,595 --> 01:04:02,055
What's the matter?
What happened?

1415
01:04:02,180 --> 01:04:04,474
Nothing, nothing, nothing.
He just took a look at me.

1416
01:04:04,599 --> 01:04:07,102
That's so funny.
He's such a good-tempered baby.

1417
01:04:07,227 --> 01:04:08,561
The doctor said
he'd never seen a baby

1418
01:04:08,686 --> 01:04:09,729
with such a wonderful
disposition.

1419
01:04:09,854 --> 01:04:11,064
Oh, I'm sure. I'm sure.

1420
01:04:11,189 --> 01:04:12,232
And it isn't because
you're a man.

1421
01:04:12,357 --> 01:04:14,692
He was smiling all over
the place at Herbert.

1422
01:04:14,818 --> 01:04:16,319
Pops?

1423
01:04:16,444 --> 01:04:18,446
Well, now, come on.
Let's blow, let's blow.

1424
01:04:18,571 --> 01:04:20,198
Pops?

1425
01:04:20,323 --> 01:04:22,158
We've come to apologize.

1426
01:04:22,283 --> 01:04:25,036
We want to say that we're
very sorry for being so rude.

1427
01:04:25,161 --> 01:04:27,288
Now, you tell him
you forgive him.

1428
01:04:27,414 --> 01:04:29,791
Come on, now, honey,
give him a great big smile.

1429
01:04:29,916 --> 01:04:32,335
Tell him how â€”

1430
01:04:32,460 --> 01:04:34,963
- Oh, you little brat.
- Oh, it's alright, darling.

1431
01:04:35,088 --> 01:04:36,631
He's gone now.
It's alright.

1432
01:04:36,756 --> 01:04:38,925
- The man is gone.
- Why do you do that?

1433
01:04:40,218 --> 01:04:41,511
You know what I think it is?

1434
01:04:41,636 --> 01:04:43,763
It's your tie.
If you just take off your tie...

1435
01:04:43,888 --> 01:04:45,432
No, Ellie, I'm not
going to take off my tie.

1436
01:04:45,557 --> 01:04:47,142
It's a perfectly nice tie,
and I happen to like it.

1437
01:04:47,267 --> 01:04:48,393
It was present from Tommy,

1438
01:04:48,518 --> 01:04:50,687
and I'm not gonna take it off
just because he doesn't like it.

1439
01:04:50,812 --> 01:04:52,147
Oh, Stanley, the way you talk.

1440
01:04:52,272 --> 01:04:54,190
He's a baby,
an innocent little baby.

1441
01:04:54,315 --> 01:04:55,775
He doesn't know what it is
that disturbs him.

1442
01:04:55,900 --> 01:04:58,069
He is not an innocent
little baby.

1443
01:04:58,194 --> 01:05:00,697
He's an individual with very
definite likes and dislikes.

1444
01:05:00,822 --> 01:05:02,449
As an individual,
I respect his right

1445
01:05:02,574 --> 01:05:03,992
to have likes and dislikes.

1446
01:05:04,117 --> 01:05:07,454
But I also reserve the right
to have a few of my own.

1447
01:05:07,579 --> 01:05:10,248
From that time on,
I gave him a wide berth.

1448
01:05:11,916 --> 01:05:13,460
It was live and let live
between us

1449
01:05:13,585 --> 01:05:15,795
until one weekend
six months later.

1450
01:05:27,265 --> 01:05:28,433
This the Banks house?

1451
01:05:28,558 --> 01:05:30,894
Well, yes, but, uh, whâ€”

1452
01:05:46,075 --> 01:05:48,870
Hello! Thank you.

1453
01:05:48,995 --> 01:05:50,455
Good evening, Mr. Banks.

1454
01:05:51,372 --> 01:05:52,916
See you tomorrow.

1455
01:06:01,758 --> 01:06:04,427
The thing I had feared
had come to pass.

1456
01:06:04,552 --> 01:06:07,847
He had invaded
the sanctity of my home.

1457
01:06:07,972 --> 01:06:09,015
Hi, Pops.

1458
01:06:09,140 --> 01:06:10,600
Hi, hi, Kay.

1459
01:06:11,893 --> 01:06:13,269
